<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><?workdir /C:\PHEMI-docs\docs\mgmt_console_user_guide\temp\pdf\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\Users?><?workdir-uri file:/C:/PHEMI-docs/docs/mgmt_console_user_guide/temp/pdf/oxy_ex-1/_Common_Source/Users/?><?path2project ..\..\..\?><?path2project-uri ../../../?><concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="concept_user-authorizations" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2" domains="(topic concept)                            (topic hi-d)                             (topic ut-d)                             (topic indexing-d)                            (topic hazard-d)                            (topic abbrev-d)                            (topic pr-d)                             (topic sw-d)                            (topic ui-d)    " class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\Users\con_user-authorizations.xml" xtrc="concept:1;3:43">
 <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\Users\con_user-authorizations.xml" xtrc="title:1;4:9">User Authorizations</title>
 <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\Users\con_user-authorizations.xml" xtrc="conbody:1;5:11">
    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\_Glossary\con_glossary.xml" xtrc="p:4;22:34">User authorizations are configurable attributes you can assign to
              <ph class="- topic/ph " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\_Variables\PHEMI_Central\con_Product-Vars.xml" xtrc="ph:1;6:48">PHEMI Central</ph> users. Authorizations are defined in <ph class="- topic/ph " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\_Variables\PHEMI_Central\con_Product-Vars.xml" xtrc="ph:1;6:48">PHEMI Central</ph> by the <ph class="- topic/ph " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\_Variables\PHEMI_Central\con_Product-Vars.xml" xtrc="ph:5;11:50">PHEMI Administrator</ph>,
            who sets them in accordance with the organization's governance policies. </p>
    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\Users\con_user-authorizations.xml" xtrc="p:2;7:8">User authorizations are used together with data visibilities to create access policies. The
      access policy matches the authorization against the data visibility to determine what action,
      if any, a user may take with respect to accessing the data. </p>
    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\Users\con_user-authorizations.xml" xtrc="p:3;10:8">Some examples of possible user authorizations are as follows: </p>
    <ul id="ul_lsz_53w_kq" class="- topic/ul " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\Users\con_user-authorizations.xml" xtrc="ul:1;11:28">
      <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\Users\con_user-authorizations.xml" xtrc="li:1;12:11"><keyword class="- topic/keyword " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\Users\con_user-authorizations.xml" xtrc="keyword:1;12:20">C_LEVEL</keyword>: The user is a C-Level individual (for example, CEO, COO, CIO,
        or CTO) with a privileged level of access. Individuals with <keyword class="- topic/keyword " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\Users\con_user-authorizations.xml" xtrc="keyword:2;13:78">C_LEVEL</keyword>
        authorization, for example, might be permitted to read data with
          <keyword class="- topic/keyword " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\Users\con_user-authorizations.xml" xtrc="keyword:3;15:20">CONFIDENTIAL</keyword> visibility.</li>
      <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\Users\con_user-authorizations.xml" xtrc="li:2;16:11"><keyword class="- topic/keyword " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\Users\con_user-authorizations.xml" xtrc="keyword:4;16:20">DOCTOR</keyword>: A user with <keyword class="- topic/keyword " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\Users\con_user-authorizations.xml" xtrc="keyword:5;16:59">DOCTOR</keyword> authorization might, for
        example, be permitted to read any information, including personally identifiable information
        or personal health information.</li>
      <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\Users\con_user-authorizations.xml" xtrc="li:3;19:11"><keyword class="- topic/keyword " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\Users\con_user-authorizations.xml" xtrc="keyword:6;19:20">ANALYST</keyword>: A user with <keyword class="- topic/keyword " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\Users\con_user-authorizations.xml" xtrc="keyword:7;19:60">ANALYST</keyword> authorization might be
        restricted to accessing only the de-identified or nonidentified data.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\Users\con_user-authorizations.xml" xtrc="p:4;22:8">A user can be assigned multiple authorizations. User authorizations are set by the <ph class="- topic/ph " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\_Variables\PHEMI_Central\con_Product-Vars.xml" xtrc="ph:5;11:50">PHEMI Administrator</ph> during system configuration. </p>
    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\Users\con_user-authorizations.xml" xtrc="p:5;24:8">All users are assigned the predefined PUBLIC authorization by default. The PUBLIC
      authorization can subsequently be removed by the <ph class="- topic/ph " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\_Variables\PHEMI_Central\con_Product-Vars.xml" xtrc="ph:5;11:50">PHEMI Administrator</ph>.</p>
    <note class="- topic/note " xtrf="C:\Users\Lindsay\AppData\Local\Temp\OxygenXMLTemp\ditaTemporaryOutputDir-1424849370215\t1\t2\t3\t4\t5\oxy_ex-1\_Common_Source\Users\con_user-authorizations.xml" xtrc="note:1;26:11">Once defined, a user authorization setting may be neither edited nor deleted. The
      description may be subsequently edited.</note>
